The paper deals with fixed-parameter tractability, polynomial kernels, and kernel lower bounds for graph modification problems, which are all topics typically studied in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of fractal structures suggests a possible connection to computational geometry, which is covered in cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also deals with graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.GT (Graph Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
